type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"As with test-driven-development (TDD), BDD is ideally written before the\nimplementation, and this is one of the big take-aways for me: where I would TDD\nwith small examples working towards a complete feature, BDD works best if the\nend-result is written first: if the "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Then ..."}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" is defined first, it is easier to\nfocus only on the absolute necessary "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Given"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"s and "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"When"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"s‚Äîa point that the\nbooks stresses at multiple occasions: focus on keeping scenarios brief (or\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"BRIEF"}],"tagName":"code","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", the acronym that is used in the book)."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#bdd-is-for-everyone-and-any-time","ariaLabel":"bdd is for everyone and any time permalink","className":["anchor","before"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"BDD is for everyone, and any time"}],"tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"bdd-is-for-everyone-and-any-time","style":"position:relative;"},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You should pick up this book today and learn about this tool, because it can be\nintroduced in a project at any time: a chapter about legacy code is included."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I especially liked their description of how feature files can serve different\naudiences and pick them up where they need the documentation to be, for example\nusing a different domain language, or (how I typically use BDD) on a lower\nlevel, without implementing steps but driving an API client."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"While most of the book centers around writing feature files that can be used to\ndrive automation tests, the author specifically mention the importance of\ntesters and their expertise, because it is not about automating tests, but about\naligning all stakeholders and the software that is getting build:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Never underestimate the domain knowledge of the people who worked on the\nproject. Testers in particular will have acquired a deep understanding of the\nproduct through their time spent testing it."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"chil